message_1: What is the Hodge number for a Calabi-Yau threefold that has mirror symmetry to another Calabi-Yau threefold with Hodge number h11 = 100 and h21 = 2?
message_2: In the context of mirror symmetry for Calabi-Yau threefolds, the Hodge numbers (h11 and h21) of the original threefold and its mirror partner are interchanged. So, if the original Calabi-Yau threefold has Hodge numbers h11 = 100 and h21 = 2, then its mirror symmetric Calabi-Yau threefold will have Hodge numbers h11 = 2 and h21 = 100.
